  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "QC Laboratory Supervisor",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<p>The <strong>QC Laboratory Supervisor</strong> is responsible   for the day-to-day operations of the laboratory and ensure compliance to   operating standards.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Coordinate   the day-to-day activities of a team of Laboratory Assistants who check, test,   and inspect raw material, goods in process and finished products.</li>\n  <li>Prioritize   and assign tasks to ensure that team’s resources are used effectively, and   that work schedules and targets are met.</li>\n  <li>Assists   QC Manager in classification of final product and reworked lots.</li>\n  <li>Responsible   for troubleshooting and investigating quality issues, implement improvement   from Analysis gap study.</li>\n  <li>Monitor   in-process samples, liaison with production teams for preventive &amp;   corrective actions.</li>\n  <li>Prepare   activity and progression reports so recurring problems, either with the   quality of the product or the reliability of testing procedures, can be   identified and addressed.</li>\n  <li>Monitor   the performance of staff, equipment and laboratory processes to ensure quality   control system effectiveness and efficiency.</li>\n  <li>Preparation   of quality and budget reports and updates.</li>\n  <li>Training   of all lab assistants and shift technicians assigned to laboratory work.</li>\n  <li>Supervise   and coach team members.</li>\n  <li>Supports   QC department functions onsite and off-site as necessary.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Our Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or Degree in Chemical related field.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 5 years’ hands-on experience in Laboratory Testing (Wet Chemistry).</li>\n  <li>Good understanding of laboratory equipment such as GC, AAS, Auto-titrator, NIR etc.</li>\n  <li>Manual Testing, we do not use automated testing machine.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Key competency:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Ability to supervise and lead a team of Laboratory Assistants.</li>\n  <li>Good analytical, troubleshooting, and problem-solving skills.</li>\n  <li>Ability to work independently under pressure in a very fast pace Chemical Manufacturing QC environment and meet tight deadlines.</li>\n  <li>Strong communication skills, both written and verbal.</li>\n  <li>Cross-functional collaboration</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 5,
